stagecoach became the first in the series of seven classic ford westerns filmed on location in monument valley,the other ford westerns with location work shot in monument valley were my darling clementine ( 1946 ) , fort apache ( 1948 ) , she wore a yellow ribbon ( 1949 ) , the searchers ( 1956 ) , sergeant rutledge ( 1960 ) , and cheyenne autumn ( 1964 ) .

the movies : this classic john ford western features cathy downs as clementine

